00:10:28.120 --> 00:10:31.039
And all this to say that either you focus on your strengths

00:10:31.422 --> 00:10:34.559
and become number 1, the best in your niche.

00:10:34.982 --> 00:10:36.159
And for that, there's no secret.

00:10:36.461 --> 00:10:37.732
You have to work, sharpen, refine.

00:10:40.379 --> 00:10:42.360
Keep working on your strengths.

00:10:43.081 --> 00:10:46.299
And then, you surround yourself with people who aren't as good in other areas

00:10:46.320 --> 00:10:47.879
since you won't be able to do just that.

00:10:48.299 --> 00:10:48.677
Alright?

00:10:49.101 --> 00:10:51.860
To pull off a project, you need people in sales,

00:10:52.059 --> 00:10:53.139
you need people in the back office,

00:10:53.360 --> 00:10:54.200
you need people with vision,

00:10:54.379 --> 00:10:56.580
you need Excel files, you need accountants, you need legal people.

00:10:56.880 --> 00:10:58.799
Everything has to work together.

00:10:59.541 --> 00:11:01.078
So, nobody's good at everything.

00:11:01.721 --> 00:11:02.719
And my advice to you, anyway,

00:11:02.980 --> 00:11:04.778
so school number 1 is Focus Strengths.

00:11:05.280 --> 00:11:08.139
School number 2 is the generalist, the one who...

00:11:08.259 --> 00:11:10.120
Well, we need them too, we need conductors,

00:11:10.159 --> 00:11:11.052
we need people who are generalists,

00:11:11.761 --> 00:11:13.139
who are kind of a jack-of-all-trades.

00:11:13.721 --> 00:11:16.200
But in business, when you focus on your strengths,

00:11:16.320 --> 00:11:17.539
that's where it's going to help you.

00:11:18.201 --> 00:11:22.519
And those who choose not to develop their talents, their skills, etc.

00:11:23.041 --> 00:11:25.360
because they think they can make up for it with other tasks,

00:11:25.923 --> 00:11:27.438
